The paper proposes a novel deep neural network architecture for semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task (cs.CV). The algorithm uses semi-supervised learning, which involves training with both labeled and unlabeled data, and this is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The approach also involves decoupling classification and segmentation tasks, which is a design choice that falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of activation maps, which are a common tool in neural network optimization and training, and this falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on the PASCAL VOC dataset, which is a widely used benchmark in multimedia research (cs.MM).
